The '''white-streaked friarbird''' ('''''Melitograis gilolensis''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Meliphagidae]]. It is [[monotypic]] within the genus '''''Melitograis'''''.<ref name = "ITIS"/> It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Northern Maluku]] in [[Indonesia]].<ref name = "HBW"/> Its natural [[habitat]]s are subtropical or tropical moist lowland [[forest]]s, subtropical or tropical mangrove forests, and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s.<ref name="iucn status 12 November 2021" />

